div.p:
     Confederation means to Official Members a pension; to the people it means self-government; 


     and I say, Sir, that above all things, we must keep in view the absolute necessity of keeping 


     control of our own local affairs, otherwise Confederation would be useless to the country; 


     and I warn Hon. Members at the other side of the House, that to exclude Responsible Govern
ment from the terms is to ensure defeat for the whole Confederation scheme when it comes 


     before the people at the polls.
